Shlaudeman, who has served as ambassador to Argentina, Peru, Brazil and Venezuela, is a premier State Department specialist on Latin America and is expected to win easy Senate confirmation. The Bush administration is expected to name career diplomat Harry Shlaudeman as the first US ambassador to Nicaragua in almost two years, a US official says. The administration had planned to send another career diplomat, Melissa Wells, to Managua but had a change of heart after concluding she might face a prolonged Senate confirmation fight because she has been a target of conservatives.  Jesse Helms, R-NC. 